{%- doc -%}
  Outputs a comma-separated list of CSS timeline names for use as the value of
  the `timeline-scope` CSS property on a slideshow container. Each entry is
  `--<prefix>-<i>` for i in [0, count - 1].

  Matches the 0-based naming convention used by snippets/slideshow-slide.liquid,
  which sets `--slideshow-timeline: --slide-{{ index }}` where `index` is
  `forloop.index0` from the parent gallery loop.

  @param {number} count - Number of timelines to scope.
  @param {string} prefix - Name prefix (without leading dashes).

  @example
  {% render 'timeline-scope', count: 5, prefix: 'slide' %}
  → --slide-0, --slide-1, --slide-2, --slide-3, --slide-4
{%- enddoc -%}
{%- liquid
  if count and count > 0
    assign last_index = count | minus: 1
    for i in (0..last_index)
      echo '--'
      echo prefix
      echo '-'
      echo i
      unless forloop.last
        echo ', '
      endunless
    endfor
  endif
-%}
